Jeanelle Greyling, Netwerk24A photo of Piet Byleveld taken just hours hours before he was admitted to hospital. (Elizabeth Sejake, Rapport) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - Former top cop Piet Byleveld is being &ldquo;kept comfortable&rdquo; in the Wilgeheuwel Hospital in Roodepoort, but there &ldquo;is nothing more doctors can do for him&rdquo;, his wife Elize and daughter Virnalize Welthagen told Netwerk24 on Sunday morning.&ldquo;He isn&rsquo;t doing well at all,&rdquo; said Welthagen.Byleveld, 67, who was struggling to breathe, was admitted to the hospital on Tuesday evening, according to Rapport.&ldquo;Piet Byl&rdquo;, as he is also known, was diagnosed with phase 4 lung cancer on March 10.There is also a big tumour in his liver, which has spread to his adrenal gland and spine, Rapport reported.Byleveld retired in 2010 after a career in the police spanning 38 years.&nbsp;Cases in which he was involved, included the investigation into the murder of Leigh Matthews, &nbsp;Sibille Zanner and Sheldean Human, as well as serial killers Cedric Maake and Lazarus Mazingane, the Nasrec murderer.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.